🛡️ Penetration Testing and Exploitation using Metasploit Framework

📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates penetration testing and exploitation techniques using Metasploit Framework. It is an advanced security tool used to identify, validate, and exploit vulnerabilities in systems in a controlled and ethical environment.

The project focuses on understanding how attackers exploit vulnerabilities and how security professionals test systems to strengthen defenses.

🎯 Objectives

Understand the concept of penetration testing and exploitation
Identify vulnerabilities in a target system
Exploit vulnerabilities using controlled payloads
Analyze system behavior after exploitation
Demonstrate post-exploitation techniques

🧠 Concept

Penetration testing involves simulating real-world cyber attacks to identify weaknesses in a system.

Metasploit works by
Using exploit modules to target vulnerabilities
Delivering payloads to gain access
Executing post-exploitation techniques
Providing a structured framework for testing

⚙️ Tools and Technologies Used

